00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:04,219
It was a warm afternoon in Baker Street and the hum of wheels upon the Marylebone Road

00:00:04,219 --> 00:00:06,390
came through our open window like a constant.

00:00:06,390 --> 00:00:09,859
Vention drummer marking time for London's immeasurable heart.

00:00:09,859 --> 00:00:14,219
Owens lay at length upon the sofa, his keen eyes half-lidded.

00:00:14,219 --> 00:00:18,300
The violin at his side, as though it were a sword, sheathed after some brisk engagement

00:00:18,300 --> 00:00:22,980
while I, ever the pupil, poured over a botany monograph he had placed in my hands

00:00:22,980 --> 00:00:26,820
to demonstrate how ash upon a man's cuff could betray not only his trade

00:00:26,820 --> 00:00:31,539
but his parish and his habits of weathering and exercise he insisted was excellent for the muscles

00:00:31,539 --> 00:00:38,640
of attention my dear watson if the monograph bores you close it with a clear conscience

00:00:38,640 --> 00:00:46,740
a muscle overstrained is as unfit for service as one untrained and i would rather you kept your

00:00:46,740 --> 00:00:53,679
powers supple for something more diverting that is presently ascending our stare i started at that

00:00:53,679 --> 00:00:59,560
for I had heard no bell and seen no shadow, and I ventured to ask him how he came by his certainty

00:00:59,560 --> 00:01:04,239
that a visitor was upon us, and what manner of visitor it might be to draw his interest

00:01:04,239 --> 00:01:10,219
from the idle doper which sometimes claimed him between cases. The aroma of Otto, of violet

00:01:10,219 --> 00:01:17,120
mingled with a faint whiff of coal gas from a private carriage lamp, the delicate scrib

00:01:17,120 --> 00:01:27,659
clib of a narrow heel that has recently had its lift renewed, and a flutter of kid glove against

00:01:27,659 --> 00:01:34,359
gourd-cloth, the housemaid's breath caught twice at the landing, which she does only when a

00:01:34,359 --> 00:01:42,299
personage of consequence appears in some is a lady of rank coming in haste with a matter she

00:01:42,299 --> 00:01:49,079
she thinks romantic, but which the law would call practical, and I, for one, am grateful to romance

00:01:49,079 --> 00:01:57,159
for the practice it affords. Mr. Sherlock Holmes, Dr. being Comet, Watson, forgive this intrusion

00:01:57,159 --> 00:02:03,040
at such an hour, yet the hour presses me more rudely than my conscience. I am Violet, Duchess

00:02:03,040 --> 00:02:08,060
of Ravenscar, and I am sorely plagued by a masquerade that has leapt the footlights to tread

00:02:08,060 --> 00:02:11,740
at the boards of life, a masquerade that calls itself Prince Charming.

00:02:11,740 --> 00:02:38,060
...........................

00:02:38,060 --> 00:02:46,000
can afford to droot how this courtly prince has come to offend your house it began sir with letters

00:02:46,000 --> 00:02:51,340
that promised deliverance from dullness and a rain of happiness that seemed penned by a playwright

00:02:51,340 --> 00:02:58,840
they were addressed not to me but to my niece lady beatrice waven scar who is of an age to dream

00:02:58,840 --> 00:03:06,280
and i fear to pay for dreaming a masked figure calling himself prince charming contrived to

00:03:06,280 --> 00:03:10,840
meet her on the terrace of my London house after a charity ball and pressed upon her

00:03:10,840 --> 00:03:16,879
a crystal slipper pendant set with small diamonds. Last evening the pendant vanished. A second

00:03:16,879 --> 00:03:22,120
note arrived, you Anna? And this time there wasn't it a threat that if she did not meet

00:03:22,120 --> 00:03:30,539
him as commanded at midnight by the Cleopatra's needle, he would reveal matters that would

00:03:30,539 --> 00:03:32,219
would destroy her reputation.

00:03:32,219 --> 00:03:33,560
..

00:03:33,560 --> 00:03:36,020
Holmes turned the pasteboard under his long fingers

00:03:36,020 --> 00:03:37,810
and the thin lips compressed lightly,

00:03:37,810 --> 00:03:40,360
like a violinist hearing a false note slip

00:03:40,360 --> 00:03:41,800
within a difficult phrase.

00:03:41,800 --> 00:03:42,969
And in that instant,

00:03:42,969 --> 00:03:44,719
I realized that what had stirred him

00:03:44,719 --> 00:03:46,699
was not a question of petty romance,

00:03:46,699 --> 00:03:48,620
but a scent of organized villainy

00:03:48,620 --> 00:03:50,879
dressed out in theatrical tinsels.

00:03:50,879 --> 00:03:52,490
Your Grace,

00:03:52,490 --> 00:03:55,629
this silver dust upon the edge is not silver,

00:03:55,629 --> 00:03:58,759
but powdered tin from a cheap theatrical milliner.

00:03:58,759 --> 00:04:01,050
The glue is of a common French.

00:04:01,050 --> 00:04:04,230
Make rarely sold in London except to costumiers.

00:04:04,230 --> 00:04:07,769
There is, hmm, moreover, hmm,

00:04:07,769 --> 00:04:11,780
a faint granularity that tells of flower-stage confetti

00:04:11,780 --> 00:04:13,870
that has been trampled and swept.

00:04:13,870 --> 00:04:17,439
I venture we have to do with a person who passes with ease

00:04:17,439 --> 00:04:20,950
between the green room and the drawing-room trower.

00:04:20,950 --> 00:04:25,199
And who knows that London ladies are most credulous

00:04:25,199 --> 00:04:29,220
when the footlights of imagination are upon them.

00:04:29,220 --> 00:04:33,759
We had the misfortune to attend a pantomime at the Savoy last week

00:04:33,759 --> 00:04:37,420
where a certain actor, adored by the town,

00:04:37,420 --> 00:04:43,129
played a prince with a slipper that set the audience laughing and sighing.

00:04:43,129 --> 00:04:46,240
My niece has a taste for that sort of nonsense.

00:04:46,240 --> 00:04:47,300
..

00:04:47,300 --> 00:04:51,699
Yet I cannot believe the player himself would sink to extortion

00:04:51,699 --> 00:04:56,110
and still my house is haunted by this foolish symbol.

00:04:56,110 --> 00:05:00,259
I asked, perhaps with less tact than the situation warranted,

00:05:00,259 --> 00:05:03,180
whether Lady Beatrice had ever given cause for scandal

00:05:03,180 --> 00:05:05,879
and the Duchess answered with the cold dignity of her class

00:05:05,879 --> 00:05:09,810
that the child's only scandal was innocence carried to the verge of imprudence,

00:05:09,810 --> 00:05:14,980
quality which, as a medical man, I have seen draw more trouble than malice ever could.

00:05:14,980 --> 00:05:17,779
You have the second letter, your grace.

00:05:17,779 --> 00:05:22,639
Let us hear its voice, for paper is a superb confessional,

00:05:22,639 --> 00:05:27,319
when the writer is vain and the ink has not fully dried on his conceit.

00:05:27,319 --> 00:05:29,359
...

00:05:29,359 --> 00:05:36,039
Sir, you will observe it is scented, and that certain words are underlined with a playful hand,

00:05:36,039 --> 00:05:40,680
it commands Beatrice to come alone, to wear white,

00:05:40,680 --> 00:05:46,420
and to carry with her a small gasket of heirloom jewels as pledge

00:05:46,420 --> 00:05:51,769
and it assures her that all will be merry as a Christmas pantomime if she comply.

00:05:51,769 --> 00:05:55,300
Holmes raised the letter to his nostrils and then to the light

00:05:55,300 --> 00:05:58,680
and at last held it flat while he measured the spacing with the blade of his knife

00:05:58,680 --> 00:05:59,939
as though it were a yardstick.

00:05:59,939 --> 00:06:02,889
He tapped the margin twice and then smiled without mirth.

00:06:02,889 --> 00:06:08,360
Observe, Watson, the faint transliteration where another sheet has pressed upon it.

00:06:08,360 --> 00:06:12,600
This man keeps a ledger and writes his commands upon a pad

00:06:12,600 --> 00:06:17,420
Tearing off the page and leaving the ghost of his commerce upon the next

00:06:17,420 --> 00:06:23,040
The underlining is not caprice but code for the placement of a rendezvous guard

00:06:23,040 --> 00:06:27,000
These two underlines signal the embankment stair

00:06:27,000 --> 00:06:31,839
And the final flourish denotes the hour as the stroke

00:06:31,839 --> 00:06:34,939
Not five minutes past or before

00:06:34,939 --> 00:06:38,240
For such precision betrays a military sense

00:06:38,240 --> 00:06:42,250
mated to a theatrical taste, jela kulda.

00:06:42,250 --> 00:06:47,079
A union not uncommon in certain bankrupt officers

00:06:47,079 --> 00:06:50,220
out of India who have learned to drill illusions

00:06:50,220 --> 00:06:52,300
as once they drilled men.

00:06:52,300 --> 00:06:53,620
..

00:06:53,620 --> 00:06:56,660
Mr. Herm, Holmes, can you protect my niece

00:06:56,660 --> 00:06:59,009
without parading her name before the newspapers?

00:06:59,009 --> 00:07:02,240
For I would sooner risk my fortune than her good repute

00:07:02,240 --> 00:07:05,079
and I know not where to turn but to your singular methods

00:07:05,079 --> 00:07:07,839
which all London praises and half believes.

00:07:07,839 --> 00:07:08,900
..

00:07:08,900 --> 00:07:11,120
You did perfectly to come.

00:07:11,120 --> 00:07:13,529
We shall not consult the newspapers,

00:07:13,529 --> 00:07:17,100
but we may consult the Savoy and the Needle

00:07:17,100 --> 00:07:20,159
and one or two alleyways that run between.

00:07:20,159 --> 00:07:24,800
And if we meet our prince, we shall bow low and, I trust,

00:07:24,800 --> 00:07:28,310
pick his pocket of every pretense he carries.

00:07:28,310 --> 00:07:30,560
The Duchess drew forth another object,

00:07:30,560 --> 00:07:35,839
Then, a slipper charm of crystal cleverly cut to catch the light, and on its toe, a

00:07:35,839 --> 00:07:39,959
nick so minute that I would not have noticed it had it not been set at the very point like

00:07:39,959 --> 00:07:40,409
a dimple.

00:07:40,409 --> 00:07:44,550
She said it was the token first given, and that Beatrice had kept it like a schoolgirl.

00:07:44,550 --> 00:07:51,319
This nick is not a flaw, but a maker's sign, scratched with a needle by one who believes

00:07:51,319 --> 00:07:52,210
in private.

00:07:52,210 --> 00:07:52,709
Ha!

00:07:52,709 --> 00:07:52,920
Ha!

00:07:52,920 --> 00:08:03,920
ill marks we shall look for its twin and finding it shall find the hand that held the needle watson your hat your grace

00:08:03,920 --> 00:08:16,660
send lady beatrice to her aunt's house in bayswater for the evening and trust us to keep the midnight appointment you fear so we shall not keep it exactly in the manner commanded

00:08:16,660 --> 00:08:23,610
I am in your debt, gentlemen. I shall remove Beatrice at once and hold myself ready to receive you.

00:08:23,610 --> 00:08:32,650
And I shall pray with all the fervour that society permits that your science of deduction is as gentle with her heart as it is stern with her adversaries.

00:08:32,650 --> 00:08:39,779
The Duchess withdrew with a sweep of violet zinc and a perfume that lingered like a cord struck and still vibrating,

00:08:39,779 --> 00:08:43,100
celebrating, Contelling, Morte and Beganingses, you nutting

00:08:43,100 --> 00:08:43,750
veer!

00:08:43,750 --> 00:08:49,500
Hm! and Holmes, with that sudden accession of energy, which I had come to associate with

00:08:49,500 --> 00:08:53,899
the scent of the chase, sprang up, took down his inverness, and thrust into his pocket

00:08:53,899 --> 00:08:58,519
a small lens, a lent of strong black cord, and a packet of those curious handcuffs of

00:08:58,519 --> 00:09:03,019
his own design, which had before now shut upon wrists that thought themselves as nimble

00:09:03,019 --> 00:09:03,500
as eels.

00:09:03,500 --> 00:09:09,899
The Savoy, Watson, if our Prince has learned his manners upon the stage,

00:09:09,899 --> 00:09:15,379
the stage will betray him with a frankness the drawing-room never would.

00:09:15,379 --> 00:09:19,759
Then our tour of the green-room will still teach us

00:09:19,759 --> 00:09:25,100
what flower clings to a cheap crown and what paste to a counterfeit heart.

00:09:25,100 --> 00:09:26,700
..

00:09:26,700 --> 00:09:30,370
London that afternoon wore its familiar mask of indifference.

00:09:30,370 --> 00:09:33,339
The cabman slouch, the newsboys cry.

00:09:33,339 --> 00:09:37,899
The rivers drowned patience, and yet to me it seemed as if every cornice were an eyebrow

00:09:37,899 --> 00:09:41,169
and every lamp a lid lowered over a conspirator's wink.

00:09:41,169 --> 00:09:44,639
For I knew that in the metropolis the romance of the theatre

00:09:44,639 --> 00:09:48,629
and the precision of crime have often taken the same handsome to their rendezvous.

00:09:48,629 --> 00:09:54,279
You observe, Watson, here, how the ash of this driver's cigar

00:09:54,279 --> 00:09:57,609
flicks into wedgelets rather than moat.

00:09:57,609 --> 00:09:59,279
He smokes a cheap.

00:09:59,279 --> 00:10:01,720
...

00:10:01,720 --> 00:10:07,639
If he were to turn his head, we should see a burn on his right labelle, where he knocks

00:10:07,639 --> 00:10:13,779
away the ash with his forefinger, which, I might add, he would not do if he were left-handed.

00:10:13,779 --> 00:10:20,129
The city is an alphabet, and we advance only as we consent to learn our letters.

00:10:20,129 --> 00:10:24,740
We alighted at the Savoy and were admitted backstage by an old watchman who recognized

00:10:24,740 --> 00:10:30,480
in homes the authority of one who is never refused twice. Within, the word altered, for here were the

00:10:30,480 --> 00:10:35,659
raw and intimate limbs of illusion ropes, flats, plaster crowns, and that compound odor of grease

00:10:35,659 --> 00:10:41,159
paint, damp canvas, and stale bouquets that speaks of triumph and disappointment sleeping in the same

00:10:41,159 --> 00:10:49,320
trunk. Good evening. We seek Mr. Lionel Vale of the company, the gentleman whose prince charming

00:10:49,320 --> 00:10:56,909
has lately fluttered a number of foolish hearts in higher boxes than you are accustomed to admire from the pit.

00:10:56,909 --> 00:11:01,569
Sir, I am he, though I blush to own that my flutterings are but the joint endeavour of author,

00:11:01,569 --> 00:11:07,819
Taylor, and limelight, to what happy mischance do I owe a visit from Mr. Fom, Mr. Fom, Mr. Sherlock Holmes,

00:11:07,819 --> 00:11:10,840
whose praises are sung even in our paint-stained realm.

00:11:10,840 --> 00:11:16,539
Hmm, Mr. Well, it is not your art, I question, but a parody of it.

00:11:16,539 --> 00:11:32,460
someone has taken your princely wares to market in the open streets has any stranger asked to purchase one of your glass slippers not in the lobby shop but out of hours and in such a manner as would tickle a conscience even less fastidious than your own

00:11:32,460 --> 00:11:34,220
By your leave, sir.

00:11:34,220 --> 00:11:38,240
Some fortnight-pastor fellow with a cavalry moustache and a gait like a drill sergeant

00:11:38,240 --> 00:11:40,900
came to my dressing room with a notion to buy an old prop slipper.

00:11:40,900 --> 00:11:43,710
Saying he craved it as a keepsake for a lady who dreamed of the stage,

00:11:43,710 --> 00:11:46,019
I thought him an honest, if theatrical, admirer.

00:11:46,019 --> 00:11:49,360
But our property master denied him, for the slippers belonged to the house.

00:11:49,360 --> 00:11:51,529
Hones's eyes brightened at that description.

00:11:51,529 --> 00:11:52,250
Aye!

00:11:52,250 --> 00:11:54,650
And he fingered the Christou charm in his pocket,

00:11:54,650 --> 00:11:57,039
as if measuring it against an unseen pattern.

00:11:57,039 --> 00:12:00,039
Then he asked if there had been any thefts among the properties,

00:12:00,039 --> 00:12:02,799
or a surplus of confetti, unlike the house's own.

00:12:02,799 --> 00:12:06,039
Archie, it was a sack of confetti gone astray three nights ago,

00:12:06,039 --> 00:12:08,620
and a dresser dismissed for pilfering flour for some prank.

00:12:08,620 --> 00:12:10,740
Also, there came to us a lady journalist

00:12:10,740 --> 00:12:13,089
seeking notes for a column on the morals of the theatre,

00:12:13,089 --> 00:12:15,460
though she had more of the student than the scold about her,

00:12:15,460 --> 00:12:16,960
and she asked very particular questions

00:12:16,960 --> 00:12:20,100
about how one gains entry to a grand house under a mask.

00:12:20,100 --> 00:12:22,549
Her name, if you please,

00:12:22,549 --> 00:12:26,009
and whether she wore upon her wrist a narrow black ribbon,

00:12:26,009 --> 00:12:28,399
such as certain ladies of the pen,

00:12:28,399 --> 00:12:34,000
then affect because it holds a pencil nimbly when the hands are otherwise engaged

00:12:34,000 --> 00:12:39,019
......

00:12:39,019 --> 00:12:43,059
miss sybil hart sir and she had indeed a black ribbon and a pair of eyes that would have made

00:12:43,059 --> 00:12:46,899
a moralist forgive the theater and the theater forgive the moralist in a single look but she

00:12:46,899 --> 00:12:53,360
was harmless as a sparrow i'd take my oath upon it we thanked the player and turned to go and as

00:12:53,360 --> 00:12:58,200
we passed the property room but your home's net without ceremony upon the scuff boards and with

00:12:58,200 --> 00:13:03,059
With his lens examined a line of tiny scratches that the most domestic groom would never trouble to observe,

00:13:03,059 --> 00:13:06,470
he plucked from a crack a glane of something that glinted dully.

00:13:06,470 --> 00:13:14,019
A shard from a cheap crystal mould and a powdering of tin, our prince has shod himself here, now.

00:13:14,019 --> 00:13:15,299
..

00:13:15,299 --> 00:13:22,220
Watson, to the embankment before the lamps are lit, for a staircase keeps better counsel by daylight

00:13:22,220 --> 00:13:26,600
and the river speaks more plainly in the afternoon than at midnight.

00:13:26,600 --> 00:13:33,090
night. When rogues suppose it asleep, thus began, under that deceptive warm afternoon,

00:13:33,090 --> 00:13:37,210
the adventure of the prince charming, and I confess that I felt in my very pulse,

00:13:37,210 --> 00:13:42,019
the strange mingling of innocence and calculation that runs through all such days,

00:13:42,019 --> 00:13:46,960
for what is a fairy story, but a criminal enterprise with better costumes, and what

00:13:46,960 --> 00:13:50,980
is a criminal enterprise, but a fairy story, that has mislaid its conscience,

00:13:50,980 --> 00:13:53,039
and barely remember its moral.

00:13:53,039 --> 00:13:55,639
The Thames lounged beneath the embankment

00:13:55,639 --> 00:13:56,799
like a sated python,

00:13:56,799 --> 00:13:58,899
its coils catching pewter gleams

00:13:58,899 --> 00:14:00,799
where a pallid sun worried the surface.

00:14:00,799 --> 00:14:03,539
We descended the stone stairs by Keopatra's needle

00:14:03,539 --> 00:14:05,299
and Holmes went on before me

00:14:05,299 --> 00:14:06,539
with the remorseless patience

00:14:06,539 --> 00:14:08,650
of a pointer taking scent after a rain,

00:14:08,650 --> 00:14:11,279
the wind bore upward the odor of tar,

00:14:11,279 --> 00:14:13,179
stale dread from a hawker's guard

00:14:13,179 --> 00:14:15,820
and the indefinable sourness of damstone

00:14:15,820 --> 00:14:17,610
where many feet have hesitated.

00:14:17,610 --> 00:14:18,820
Note, Watson,

00:14:18,820 --> 00:14:42,180
The chalk marks upon the third riser from the water, not the idle doodles of a child, but a system, triangles, bared, tip to tip, and, here, a circlet intersected by a dash, thieves' cant, imported from the continent, recently naturalized among certain London cracksmen who fancy themselves men of letters.

00:14:42,180 --> 00:14:59,620
I peered, and though the scrawls seemed innocent as a schoolroom slate left unattended, the arrangement, two triangles pointing east and west, the circlet, like a stubborn son held on a leash, cast a discomfort upon me as though I had deciphered a whisper not meant for my ear and found there my own name.

00:14:59,620 --> 00:15:07,120
East-West denotes the play of watchers in pairs. Sure, while the circlet with a bar declares a

00:15:07,120 --> 00:15:16,139
deposit, our Prince commands not only the lady, but her casket. This stare, then, is both rendezvous

00:15:16,139 --> 00:15:22,379
and purse. A careless convenience that will serve until the police grow interested, I think we shall

00:15:22,379 --> 00:15:28,360
rob him of the experiment tonight and provide him a debut he did not rehearse. Holmes knelt,

00:15:28,360 --> 00:15:31,159
and from the thin gap between the second and third stones

00:15:31,159 --> 00:15:35,129
drew a slender ribbon of black, kateyoth, that clung oddly.

00:15:35,129 --> 00:15:38,769
Having caught on a snag, at one end was affixed a small clasp,

00:15:38,769 --> 00:15:42,879
bright with recent purchase, and within the clasp a hard crumb of soap.

00:15:42,879 --> 00:15:49,269
The ribbon of our lady journalist, or her cousin, the soap is a better witness.

00:15:49,269 --> 00:15:56,360
It holds in its heart the faintest print of a cipher traced by a damp finger and left to dry.

00:15:56,360 --> 00:16:02,659
eye. Observe how the tiny planes pale differently where pressure lay. The message would have been

00:16:02,659 --> 00:16:08,440
mirrored to the glass to be read by the intended eye. We must reconstruct the phrase, which,

00:16:08,440 --> 00:16:14,700
with your indulgence, I will do now upon my cuff. With a pencil, he made a set of small marks,

00:16:14,700 --> 00:16:19,539
and then a series of lines joining them like stars mapped into a constellation. In no great

00:16:19,539 --> 00:16:25,179
time he had a sentence that, even to my unschooled gaze, possessed a certain sly elegance,

00:16:25,179 --> 00:16:27,360
befitting a theatrically minded villain.

00:16:27,360 --> 00:16:55,179
............................

00:16:55,179 --> 00:17:00,359
He stood and looked upon the river and the great obelisk, as if consulting antiquity for advice on more.

00:17:00,359 --> 00:17:05,809
Turned scoundrels, then he touched my sleeve and drew me toward a bench where a man of compact figure,

00:17:05,809 --> 00:17:10,759
with an impeded moustache, sat polishing a walking stick whose silver fox's head gleamed like a grin.

00:17:10,759 --> 00:17:12,380
..

00:17:12,380 --> 00:17:14,030
Good afternoon, Colonel.

00:17:14,030 --> 00:17:19,640
Let us say Colonel, for the gate informs me more accurately than the stick

00:17:19,640 --> 00:17:25,380
and allow me to recommend that a man who conducts business upon public steps

00:17:25,380 --> 00:17:30,819
should at least polish his stick where it cannot be recognized by a watchman

00:17:30,819 --> 00:17:33,490
who reads the illustrated weeklies.

00:17:33,490 --> 00:17:36,849
I do not know you and do not thank you.

00:17:36,849 --> 00:17:40,750
The river is common property and my stick is my own affair.

00:17:40,750 --> 00:17:45,140
If you have business, bring it to me through my solicitor as honest men do.

00:17:45,140 --> 00:17:50,480
My business is generally brought to me by rogues who cannot afford solicitors.

00:17:50,480 --> 00:17:56,039
Your boots, with their square toes and the longer wear upon the outer heel,

00:17:56,039 --> 00:17:59,539
declare a military drill upon hard parade grounds.

00:17:59,539 --> 00:18:01,779
Your Styx fox was engraved in Bombay.

00:18:01,779 --> 00:18:04,340
The scar on your knuckle is of a sabre's kiss,

00:18:04,340 --> 00:18:09,940
and your eye has that restless stageward glance of a man who watches exits and entrances.

00:18:09,940 --> 00:18:12,059
In short, away, away!

00:18:12,059 --> 00:18:15,889
Away, Colonel Mordaunt, late of the 17th.

00:18:15,889 --> 00:18:20,680
Now at the green room and the gambling room, the cards are upon the table.

00:18:20,680 --> 00:18:21,700
..

00:18:21,700 --> 00:18:25,500
You will find, sir, that my cards are clean, as for my past.

00:18:25,500 --> 00:18:28,470
I display it freely because it is honourable.

00:18:28,470 --> 00:18:33,590
And if I like to see a play of an evening, I do so as a patron and not as a player.

00:18:33,590 --> 00:18:37,050
Now, if you will excuse me, I must attend to dinner.

00:18:37,050 --> 00:18:41,949
He rose with a stiffness that betrayed a recent strain of the knee and walked off with more dignity.

00:18:41,949 --> 00:18:44,660
then I would have credited to a man thus accosted.

00:18:44,660 --> 00:18:47,220
Yet I saw that his hand tightened on the fox's head

00:18:47,220 --> 00:18:49,269
until the silver whitened under pressure,

00:18:49,269 --> 00:18:51,740
a sign of anger that does not end at dinner.

00:18:51,740 --> 00:18:53,840
The colonel will figure again.

00:18:53,840 --> 00:18:58,759
A man does not carry Bombay in his pocket and the theatre in his eye.

00:18:58,759 --> 00:19:01,929
Without intending to spend both upon some operation,

00:19:01,929 --> 00:19:04,230
we must discover his company.

00:19:04,230 --> 00:19:08,720
Poor princes generally travel with a colonel to carry their baggage.

00:19:08,720 --> 00:19:10,900
From the stair we went to Bayswater,

00:19:10,900 --> 00:19:15,900
Where the Duchess had lodged her niece with a common practicality that sits well upon uncommon rank,

00:19:15,900 --> 00:19:21,949
Lady Beatrice received us with that mixture of embarrassment and relief which speaks of an indiscretion unconsummated.

00:19:21,949 --> 00:19:26,799
And at once she began to protest her innocence, until home stayed her with a courtesy so grave

00:19:26,799 --> 00:19:29,860
that it made her childish protestation seem superfluous.

00:19:29,860 --> 00:19:34,339
Lady Beatrice, your reputation is not on trial here. Facts are.

00:19:34,339 --> 00:19:40,460
and facts will do you the charity of keeping your name out of the mouths of those persons

00:19:40,460 --> 00:19:47,599
who nourish themselves on scandal tell me please how the first meeting came about

00:19:47,599 --> 00:19:55,119
and why you consented to listen again when you had suspected harm sir at the charity ball the

00:19:55,119 --> 00:20:00,160
music was so bright and the air so full of laughing that when a gentleman in a silver mask

00:20:00,160 --> 00:20:12,880
bowed and recited a line from the very play we had applauded i thought it a jest sanctioned by the company he spoke of rescuing me from dullness and said that london was a pumpkin that only the bold could roll into a carriage i laughed

00:20:12,880 --> 00:20:26,519
sir as stupid girls do and later in the garden he placed the little snipper in my hand and whispered that a prince must have a pledge if he is to claim a dance for life she said this with so touching an ingenuousness that i trembled at the thought of what wolves there

00:20:26,519 --> 00:20:30,849
are in the polite woods of our capital, and I could not but think of the many little tokens,

00:20:30,849 --> 00:20:35,640
charms, flowers, pins that pass between the sexes as though they were nothing more than

00:20:35,640 --> 00:20:39,180
sparks shaken from a heart when in truth they may set houses ablaze.

00:20:39,180 --> 00:20:43,819
And when the second letter came, you did not intend to obey it,

00:20:43,819 --> 00:20:48,599
yet you feared what it threatened, and so you hesitated.

00:20:48,599 --> 00:20:53,220
Which is precisely the interval upon which blackmail fattens.

00:20:53,220 --> 00:20:58,980
May I examine your jewel casket and the place where you kept the slipper?

00:20:58,980 --> 00:21:01,259
...

00:21:01,259 --> 00:21:03,820
Hmm, certainly, mister. Hmm.

00:21:03,820 --> 00:21:07,720
Holmes, the slipper lay upon my dressing table by the looking glass.

00:21:07,720 --> 00:21:13,579
The casket is here, and you will see that the lining bears a little scratch where the charm used to rest.

00:21:13,579 --> 00:21:18,619
Holmes bent over the glass as though it were a lake from which any number of drowned truths might be.

00:21:18,619 --> 00:21:24,619
He fished, he breathed upon it, and, with the sleeve of his coat, conjured up faint smears that, to my surprise,

00:21:24,619 --> 00:21:30,210
whose resolved into letters not unlike those I had seen upon the soap-crumb at the embankment.

00:21:30,210 --> 00:21:38,190
The same cipher traced with a damp finger, and wiped in haste, and here, upon the casket's velvet,

00:21:38,190 --> 00:21:42,630
